The '''British Society of Periodontology''' is a society of [[periodontology|periodontologists]] (i.e. [[dentist]]s who specialize in treating gum diseases) in the United Kingdom. It was founded in 1949 and its aim is to "promote the art and science of [[periodontology]]". Its activities include advisory publications for professionals and the public, educational workshops, society meetings and awards for research.<!-- All content sourced from their website on various subpages...thought better to just give the website homepage as EL -->
