{{Infobox journal | title = Methods of Information in Medicine | cover = | editor = Sabine Koch | discipline = [[Medical informatics]] | abbreviation = Methods Inf. Med. | publisher = [[Schattauer Publishers]] | former_names = Medical documentation, Medizinische Dokumentation, Dokumentation in Medizin und Biologie | country = | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 1962-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.5 | impact-year = 2017 | website = https://methods.schattauer.de/en/home.html | link1 = https://methods.schattauer.de/en/contents/current-issue.html | link1-name = Online access | link2 = https://methods.schattauer.de/en/contents/archivestandard.html | link2-name = Online archive (2006-present) | link3 = https://methods.schattauer.de/en/contents/archivepremium.html | link3-name = Online archive (1962-2005) | JSTOR = | OCLC = 01643482 | LCCN = 67036993 | CODEN = MIMCAI | ISSN = 0026-1270 | eISSN = }} '''''Methods of Information in Medicine''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering research in [[medical informatics]]. It is an official journal of the [[International Medical Informatics Association]], the [[European Federation for Medical Informatics]], and the [[German Association for Medical Informatics, Biometry and Epidemiology]]. It is the oldest and longest running journal in its field.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=McCray |first1=AT |last2=Gefeller |first2=O |last3=Aronsky |first3=D |last4=Leong |first4=TY |last5=Sarkar |first5=IN |last6=Bergemann |first6=D |last7=Lindberg |first7=DA |last8=van Bemmel |first8=JH |last9=Haux |first9=R |title=The birth and evolution of a discipline devoted to information in biomedicine and health care as reflected in its longest running journal |journal=Methods of Information in Medicine |year=2011 |volume=50 |issue=6 |pages=491–507 |doi=10.3414/ME11-06-0001}}</ref>
==Abstracting and indexing== The journal is abstracted and indexed in: *[[Current Contents]]/Clinical Medicine<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2017-01-07}}</ref> *[[Embase|Embase/Excerpta Medica]]<ref name=Embase>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/solutions/embase/coverage |title=Embase Coverage |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Embase |accessdate=2017-01-07}}</ref> *[[EmCare]] *[[Index Medicus]]/[[MEDLINE]]/[[PubMed]]<ref name=MEDLINE>{{cite web |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog/0210453 |title=Methods of Information in Medicine |work=NLM Catalog |publisher=[[National Center for Biotechnology Information]] |accessdate=2017-01-07}}</ref> *[[Science Citation Index]]<ref name=ISI/> *[[Scopus]]<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/online-tools/scopus/content-overview |title=Content overview |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus |accessdate=2017-01-07}}</ref> According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal had a 2014 [[impact factor]] of 2.2.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Methods of Information in Medicine |title=2014 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref> In 2015 the journal did not receive an impact factor as it was delisted because of citation stacking.<ref>{{cite web|title=Journal Citation Reports Notices |url=http://admin-apps.webofknowledge.com/JCR/static_html/notices/notices.htm |publisher=Thomson Reuters |accessdate=2017-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202191948/http://admin-apps.webofknowledge.com/JCR/static_html/notices/notices.htm |archive-date=2016-12-02 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> The 2016 impact factor subsequently fell to 1.8 <ref name=WoS16>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Methods of Information in Medicine |title=2016 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Clarivate Analytics]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref> and in the 2018 release of JCR 2017 fell further to 1.5 <ref name=WoS17>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Methods of Information in Medicine |title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Clarivate Analytics]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>.
The editors of ''Methods of Information in Medicine'' and the other journal involved, ''[[Applied Clinical Informatics]]'' published a rebuttal in an editorial in both journals.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Koch |first1=S |last2=Lehmann |first2=CU |last3=Haux |first3=R |title=On Bridges and Stacks |journal=Methods of Information in Medicine |year=2016 |volume=55 |issue=4 |pages=299–300 |doi=10.3414/ME16-03-0002|pmc=5052544 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Koch |first1=S |last2=Lehmann |first2=CU |last3=Haux |first3=R |title=On Bridges and Stacks |journal=Applied Clinical Informatics |year=2016 |volume=7 |issue=3 |pages=707–710 |doi=10.4338/ACI-2016-07-IE-0110|pmc=5052544 }}</ref> The president and publication officer of the [[European Federation for Medical Informatics]] also commented on this matter.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=de Lusignan |first1=S |last2=Moen |first2=A |title=Extracting Oneself from the Citation-stacking Bear Trap |journal=Methods of Information in Medicine |year=2016 |volume=55 |issue=4 |pages=301–302 |doi=10.3414/ME16-03-0001}}</ref> Phil Davis visualized the citation cartel pointing out that Lehmann and Haux (the editors of the two journals) produced a total of 4 papers in 2014 and 2015 that excessively cited each other's journal articles for the impact-factor relevant years.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Davis|first1=Phil|title=Visualizing Citation Cartels|url=https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2016/09/26/visualizing-citation-cartels/|website=Scholarly Kitchen}}</ref>
